    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–2348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="97" xml:id="d757fn97">Repeated to the Consul General at
                        Peiping on the same date as telegram No. 188.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 23, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1484. Dept no objection issuance stronger warning than that recommended Deptel
                    1457 Oct 15 if in Emb opinion such warning would have effect convincing
                    additional Americans of desirability evacuating as indicated Peiping’s 567 Oct
                        21<note n="98" xml:id="d757fn98">Sent to the Department as telegram No. 372,
                            <ref target="#pg_855">p. 855</ref>.</note> and Tientsin’s 538 Oct
                        22,<note n="99" xml:id="d757fn99">Sent to the Department as telegram No.
                        295, <ref target="#pg_856">p. 856</ref>.</note> both to Nanking. Dept in
                    suggesting changes in Emb text was governed by following two considerations: (1)
                    to avoid insofar as possible contributing to deterioration morale and
                    Nationalist position north China and (2) to avoid possibility of adding to
                    hazards of those Americans who would decide remain even under imminent Communist
                    occupation.</p>
                <p>Telegraph final text as far in advance of release as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
